|ordinum[terrestris]
  :title Ordinatio Ordinum — the Terrestris phase floor, as instituted data
  :version 0.1.0
  :status draft-until-first-pinned
  :created 2026-07-11
  :manifold cube-sphere-3d-voxel
  :reportatio .archive/PHASES.md
  :reportatio-pin 42621d5

  ; Terrestris = the earthlike world-kind — the TRACK. Its floor (this ordinum)
  ; and its conformance profile (Regula Terrestris) share the track name and
  ; are told apart by artifact type (.ordinum.udon vs .regula.udon): one track,
  ; two faces. This is ONE ordinum among a planned many in the tabularium; a
  ; second, wholly different one is anticipated (a cellular-automata testbed,
  ; likely a 2-D plane — `:manifold euclidean-plane-2d`). The SCHEMA here
  ; (phase / charge / promise / defeasance / record) is world-kind-agnostic;
  ; only the CONTENT below is Earth-lineage. One ordinum, many regulae: other
  ; profiles over the same ladder are possible.

  ; The first instituted artifact of the tabularium: the per-phase
  ; Charge/Promise floor as DATA, which every regula pins (`ordinum@version`)
  ; as the floor it may extend but never silently undercut. The whole ladder
  ; lives here; a regula SLICES its target phase from it (later phases render
  ; as horizon, never as failures). .archive/PHASES.md is this document's
  ; reportatio — the prose working text it was authorized from; a PHASES
  ; revision yields a NEW ordinum version (immutable once any regula pins
  ; one), and existing regulae opt in by re-versioning. Faithfulness to the
  ; reportatio is the governing constraint: the terms here are the reportatio's
  ; terms, verbatim in substance.

  |meta[reading-rules]

    A phase declares three things about what it hands the future — CHARGES,
    PROMISES, and DEFEASANCES — plus a RECORD (the readable-in-rock slice).

    - CHARGE — what the phase must establish; the GATING SUBSET of its
      promises. A charge IS the next phase-gate's opening condition. :tag is
      the gate tag (LEXICON §1): gate (hard prerequisite we simulate) · earth
      (Earth's pattern kept for fidelity) · mech (causality known, no
      simulable mechanism yet) · emergent (verify, don't build). Tags state
      ARROW-KIND, never implementation status — the reportatio's status asides
      ("running today", "fBm stands in") are stripped; built-status lives in
      the nomotheke and the store.

    - PROMISE — a defeasible, forward-facing commitment this phase generates,
      preconditioned on prior phases, that later phases may depend on. The
      SUPERSET of which Charge is the gating subset. Its `.class` is its kind:
      state (a frozen field/datum handed forward) · regime (nomoi that keep
      running past the gate) · capability (a precondition now unlocked that
      enables new nomoi downstream) · limit (a standing incapability in force).
      Classes stack (`.state.regime`). Within a promise:
      - `:kept-by <nomos>` — the function that makes it true. ABSENCE = GLOSS:
        an honest word-of-honor not yet mechanized. The gloss set is exactly
        the promises with no `:kept-by` — greppable, auditable for epistemic
        honesty, never mistaken for a guarantee.
      - `|predicate ...` — the testable condition a probe would check (the
        falsifiable core; prose now, formal as it sharpens).
      - `:from <charge>` — the charge that generates this promise (composition).
      - `:unlocks <charge>` — a downstream charge this capability enables.

    - PROMISE MATURITY — the acceptance-test discipline. A promise climbs a
      ladder: NAMED (prose only — the big picture laid down) -> SPECIFIED (has
      a `|predicate`; what would count as keeping it is now defined) ->
      CLAIMED (has `:kept-by`; a nomos says it delivers) -> KEPT (the predicate
      passes at a declared epistemic tier, via declared-vs-derived). The rule
      that keeps this honest: a promise with NO predicate CANNOT be marked
      fulfilled at any epistemic level — nothing has yet been defined that
      could convict it. So big-picture promises land first and their
      predicates are written when we actually need to see them delivered,
      which then guides the coding. The regula conformance audit computes each
      promise's rung and reports the gaps ("promise X: un-checkable — no
      predicate") beside the fidelity pyramid.

    - DEFEASANCE — the mechanism of "defeasible". A phase declares ONLY its
      NOVEL promises; inherited promises CONTINUE IMPLICITLY (no re-listing —
      the mind should not carry ancient ongoing processes as clutter). What a
      phase DOES retire, it says so explicitly: `|defeasance :voids
      "<phase.promise>" :by <charge>` with an honest reason. So the promises
      IN FORCE at phase N = union(promises 1..N) minus union(defeasances 1..N).
      Audit rule (same shape as a voided permit): a defeased promise whose
      `:kept-by` nomos is still consumed by a live nomos is an INCOHERENCE.
      Cross-phase references are quoted qualified ids ("N.promise-slug").

    - Structure: a phase OPENS AT the delivery of the previous phase's charges
      — each manufactures the key to the next gate. Flat, not nested; if any
      phase earns internal sub-gates it is Abyssal (:sub-gates expected).

  |phase[ante-mundane]
    :num 1
    :name Ante-mundane
    :epithet before the world
    :regime analytic
    Cosmic scale; everything prior to the world. Not a process — a parameter
    block (pure parameters: element abundances, orbital configuration, seed).
    |charge[stable-orbit] :tag gate
      Stable orbit in the habitable zone of a viable, protected system.
    |charge[proper-mass] :tag gate
      Proper mass.
    |charge[elemental-abundances] :tag gate
      Earth-like elemental abundances.
    |charge[protective-architecture] :tag mech
      Protective architecture (some implicit) — moon, outer giants, solar-wind
      shelter. The moon cannot be added non-destructively later (at least in
      real life), so it is declared here — declare-causally-materialize-lazily;
      its real services are ocean tides, moonlight and phases, and axial-tilt
      stabilization.
    |promises
      |promise[the-constants].state :from elemental-abundances
        The constants themselves — orbit, mass, chemistry, seed: the box every
        later computation happens inside.
        |predicate the Phase-1 parameter block is declared and conserved forward.
    |record
      Proportions and totals of elements, base columns, and most conserved
      values.

  |phase[protogenic]
    :num 2
    :name Protogenic
    :epithet the world is now Formed
    :regime analytic
    A sphere orbiting its star, featureless, hot, brooded upon. Sphere, tilt,
    spin, insolation rhythm as pure functions.
    |charge[axial-tilt] :tag gate
      Axial tilt.
    |charge[spin] :tag gate
      Spin — possibly differential layers (the magnetic-dynamo mechanism is
      mech-grade).
    |charge[smooth-water-surface] :tag earth
      Smooth, water-covered surface.
    |charge[insolation-rhythm] :tag emergent
      The rhythm of angle-specific solar insolation (falls out of tilt + spin
      + orbit).
    |promises
      |promise[formed-sphere].state
        The sphere itself — formed, and orbiting its star.
      |promise[water-covered-surface].state :from smooth-water-surface
        A smooth, water-covered surface.
      |promise[axial-rhythms].regime :kept-by planet :from insolation-rhythm
        Tilt and spin produce seasons and the day/night cycle, forever, and
        the angle-specific insolation rhythm with them.
        |predicate insolation, declination, and hour-angle are correct for date and latitude.
      |promise[coriolis].capability :from spin :unlocks modern-weather
        Spin bequeaths Coriolis — the skeleton of every future wind belt and
        ocean gyre.
      |promise[insolation-gradient].capability :kept-by planet :from insolation-rhythm :unlocks biogeochemical-cycles
        The latitudinal insolation gradient — the skeleton of all climate zones.

  |phase[primordial]
    :num 3
    :name Primordial
    :epithet the world is now Divided
    :regime analytic-relaxation
    Gas, liquid, and solid separate: a dense, hot, pre-oxygenation atmosphere;
    a sea level; solid ground beneath. Venus-like but far wetter. Light is
    ambient and highly diffused — day and night exist, but the sun is not yet
    seen. Reservoir partitions; water cycle settled to steady state.
    |charge[atmosphere-reservoir] :tag gate
      Atmosphere as a real reservoir, pre-oxygen composition.
    |charge[closed-water-cycle] :tag gate
      Water cycle, closed.
    |charge[weather-energy-channels] :tag gate
      Basic weather fluid dynamics; useful-energy / entropy-gradient channels.
    |charge[magnetic-shelter] :tag mech
      Magnetic field preserving the atmosphere — a canceling pair with the
      solar wind (permit territory in any regula).
    |charge[seeded-asymmetry] :tag gate
      Enough variation, asymmetry, and seeded noise to awaken the Phase-4
      processes (fated-noise machinery is this condition's instrument).
    |charge[abiogenesis] :tag earth
      Abiogenesis, through photosynthetic sea life — microbial at least.
      Joseph: Abyssal opens after this exists.
    |promises
      |promise[three-reservoirs].state :from atmosphere-reservoir
        The three reservoirs — gas, liquid, solid — and their interfaces.
      |promise[sea-level-datum].state
        The sea-level datum every later elevation is read against.
      |promise[pre-oxygen-composition].state :from atmosphere-reservoir
        The reducing, pre-oxygen atmospheric composition.
      |promise[diffused-light].regime
        Ambient, highly-diffused light — day and night exist, but the sun is
        not yet seen through the dense sky.
      |promise[closed-water-cycle].regime :from closed-water-cycle
        A closed, conserved water cycle with its energy-gradient channels.
        |predicate global water mass is conserved — nothing pulled from nothing, nothing drained into nothing.
      |promise[weather-channels].capability :from weather-energy-channels :unlocks modern-weather
        Basic weather fluid dynamics; the useful-energy / entropy-gradient
        channels later dynamics run on.
      |promise[seeded-asymmetry].capability :kept-by noise :from seeded-asymmetry :unlocks plate-tectonics
        The seeded asymmetries and fated noise that awaken the Phase-4
        processes; every later phase amplifies them.
        |predicate a deterministic, per-key asymmetry field exists and is stable under re-query.
      |promise[photosynthesizers].capability :from abiogenesis :unlocks oxygenation
        The first light-capturing microbial life — the engine of the later
        atmospheric composition shift.

  |phase[abyssal]
    :num 4
    :name Abyssal
    :epithet the world is now Alive
    :regime incremental-emergent
    :sub-gates expected
    Deep Time. The world itself becomes a highly dynamic system across great
    orders of temporal magnitude; runs long and continues beneath all later
    phases as their geological substrate. The heavyweight: its own timescale
    ladder (tectonic Myr to erosive Kyr), its own structures.
    |charge[plate-tectonics] :tag mech
      Plate tectonics and the Wegenerian cycle.
    |charge[emergent-land] :tag gate
      Meaningful non-volcanic land above sea level — delivered by uplift /
      proto-tectonic processes, never an initial condition.
    |charge[mineral-systems] :tag gate
      Mineral systems and cycles.
    |charge[erosion-carving] :tag gate
      Erosion processes carving real landscapes.
    |charge[biomineralization] :tag earth
      Sea-life complexity through biomineralization — and it is the mechanism
      of the next phase's atmosphere gate.
    |charge[oxygenation] :tag emergent
      Oxygen accumulating toward the Great Oxygenation (from the
      photosynthesizers).
    |charge[proto-biomes] :tag emergent
      Alien proto-biomes, hostile to complex life.
    |promises
      |promise[emerged-land].state :from emergent-land
        THE LAND ITSELF — continents, relief, and drainage networks; every
        future rain-shadow, watershed, and harbor is drawn here.
        |predicate land rises above sea level, non-volcanic; land-fraction toward the early-Earth target band (survey §6).
      |promise[erosion-substrate].regime :kept-by erosion-tile :from erosion-carving
        Fluvial erosion continues running as the geological substrate beneath
        every later phase.
        |predicate erosion runs each geological cycle; its eroded bed is what later phases build on.
      |promise[ore-and-soil].state :from mineral-systems
        Mineral and ore bodies; soil parent material.
      |promise[toward-breathable].capability :from oxygenation :unlocks post-oxygenation-atmosphere
        An ocean-atmosphere partway to breathable — the precondition Phase 5's
        atmosphere gate consumes.
    |defeasances
      |defeasance :voids "2.water-covered-surface" :by emergent-land
        Land now rises above the sea; the surface is no longer wholly
        water-covered.
    |record
      The deep sedimentary stack; banded-iron formations (oxygen meeting
      dissolved iron); the first limestones — life writing itself into rock.

  |phase[primeval]
    :num 5
    :name Primeval
    :epithet the world is now Awake
    :regime coupled-relaxation-emergent-weather
    The clouds part; the world beholds the cosmos for the first time — dawn,
    the morning sun, the moon in its phases, and at night the stars. The
    climate tier over the Phase-2 insolation.
    |charge[post-oxygenation-atmosphere] :tag gate
      :opened-by "4.oxygenation"
      Earth-like post-oxygenation atmosphere.
    |charge[ozone-shield] :tag emergent
      Ozone shield (from the new oxygen; the land-life prerequisite).
    |charge[visible-cosmos] :tag gate
      Sun, moon, and stars visible at true angles, phases, and seasons.
    |charge[modern-weather] :tag emergent
      Modern weather dynamics.
    |charge[biogeochemical-cycles] :tag earth
      Nitrogen and companion biogeochemical cycles.
    |charge[land-plants] :tag earth
      Stationary land life — plants colonize the continents (land is lethal
      without the ozone this phase's sky provides).
    |promises
      |promise[breathable-sky].state :from post-oxygenation-atmosphere
        A breathable sky and its ozone roof.
      |promise[ozone-roof].capability :from ozone-shield :unlocks land-plants
        The ozone shield — it makes the continents survivable for life.
      |promise[visible-cosmos].state :kept-by planet :from visible-cosmos
        Sun, moon, and stars visible at true angles, phases, and seasons — the
        clock later navigators and calendars read.
        |predicate sun, moon, and star positions are correct for date and latitude.
      |promise[modern-circulation].regime :from modern-weather
        Climate zones and modern circulation, including the coupled
        ocean-atmosphere oscillations — the droughts and monsoons later phases
        live by.
      |promise[vegetated-continents].regime :from land-plants
        Vegetated continents that change albedo and slow erosion — roots as a
        geological force.
    |defeasances
      |defeasance :voids "3.pre-oxygen-composition" :by post-oxygenation-atmosphere
        Oxygenation has converted the reducing atmosphere; the pre-oxygen
        composition no longer holds.
      |defeasance :voids "3.diffused-light" :by visible-cosmos
        The clouds part; ambient diffused light gives way to direct sun, moon,
        and stars.
    |record
      Redbeds — the oxidation event rusts the rock record; late, the first
      soil horizons under land plants.

  |phase[archaic]
    :num 6
    :name Archaic
    :epithet the world is now Abundant
    :regime statistical-ecology-to-agent-based
    Life as we know it, fully adapted to the world it helped create: agents in
    the sea, on land, in the air.
    |charge[complex-sea-life] :tag earth
      Oxygen-breathing, complex, mobile sea life — abundant and diverse.
    |charge[flight] :tag earth
      Mobile land life, through flight — birds, fowl, reptiles of every
      variety.
    |charge[evolutionary-pressures] :tag mech
      Resilient, calibrated evolutionary pressures; energy-gradient-driven
      diversity mechanisms.
    |promises
      |promise[food-web].regime :from evolutionary-pressures
        The food web and its capability set — ecological capabilities set the
        material-flux rules (decay vs burial) for everything after.
      |promise[mobile-life].state
        Complex, mobile, oxygen-breathing life in the sea, on land, and in the
        air.
      |promise[coal-window].limit :from evolutionary-pressures
        A standing limit: until lignin-digesters arrive, wood buries instead
        of rotting — a phase-window material born of a temporary inability.
        |predicate woody material accumulates (buries) rather than decaying.
    |defeasances
      |defeasance :voids "4.proto-biomes" :by complex-sea-life
        The alien proto-biomes hostile to complex life give way to abundant,
        diverse complex life.
    |record
      The fossil-bearing strata begin; coal seams, the signature of an
      inability.

  |phase[aboriginal]
    :num 7
    :name Aboriginal
    :epithet the world is now Recognizable
    :target 1
    :regime substrate-stable-beneath-agent-seam
    Earth since shortly after the Cenozoic dawn: the Age of Mammals. This is
    the phase where the primary simulations with real agent interactions begin
    — the ASF's domain.
    |charge[mammals-and-taxonomy] :tag earth
      Mammals; recognizable kingdom/taxonomy diversity across land, air, and
      sea.
    |charge[modern-flora-fungus] :tag earth
      Modern flora and fungus ecosystems — flowers and fruit, grain and seed,
      wood that decays.
    |charge[insects-microbiome] :tag earth
      Modern insect world and microbiome.
    |charge[complex-agency] :tag gate
      Complex intelligence, communication, and agency — Pleistocene-grade
      life.
    |promises
      |promise[resource-world].state
        The agent-legible resource world — food and forage, timber and fiber,
        prey and pasture, workable stone and ore: the inventory the ASF agents
        will perceive, value, and act through.
      |promise[decomposers].capability :from modern-flora-fungus
        Fungal and microbial decomposers — wood and organic matter now decay
        and cycle their nutrients.
        |predicate woody material decays and returns nutrients rather than burying.
      |promise[modern-taxonomy].state :from mammals-and-taxonomy
        Mammals; modern flora, fungus, insects, and microbiome.
    |defeasances
      |defeasance :voids "6.coal-window" :by modern-flora-fungus
        Lignin-digesting decomposers have arrived; wood now decays rather than
        burying. The coal-seam window is closed.
    |record
      Recognizable modern strata; anthropic traces only from Phase 8.

  |phase[prehistoric]
    :num 8
    :name Prehistoric
    :epithet the world now has People
    :target 2
    :regime agent-based-slow-layer-engages
    :binds ETHICS.md
    Not mankind per se, but speech, symbolic thought, emotion,
    self-determination, higher-order agency. No creature has yet frozen
    thought onto matter — none has a written language that outlives the mind
    that thought it, that could move a thought back out of the timestream the
    first phases started.
    |charge[hominid-equivalent] :tag earth
      Hominids, or an equivalently-ordered agent and intelligence.
    |charge[language] :tag gate
      Speech / language — high-enough-fidelity, adaptable, arbitrarily
      abstractable person-to-person thought transfer.
    |charge[agriculture] :tag earth
      Agriculture (likely).
    |charge[culture] :tag earth
      Non-genetic cross-generational transfer: culture; durable
      familial/tribal cohabitation.
    |obligation
      :severity load-bearing-must-survive-every-revision
      This phase-transition is where OBLIGATION BEGINS. "The world has People"
      is precisely the point at which the builder acquires duties to what is
      inside it: ETHICS.md's constraints bind from here forward. The moment an
      agent in this world is driven by the slow (LLM) layer it enters moral
      scope (doc/design/DESIGN.md, the two-layer mind). Any regula whose target
      phase is 8 or beyond inherits this bind non-negotiably; the moratorium
      (ETHICS.md) sits above it.
    |promises
      |promise[culture].regime :from culture
        Culture itself — language, names on places, domesticated lineages,
        managed landscapes, paths that become roads: inheritance that now
        travels OUTSIDE the genome.
      |promise[language].capability :from language :unlocks written-language
        Arbitrarily-abstractable, adaptable person-to-person thought transfer.
    |record
      Symbolic artifacts, hearths, worked tools — culture entering the strata,
      but not yet writing.

  |phase[scribal]
    :num 9
    :name Scribal
    :epithet the world now has Writing and history
    :target 3
    :regime author-driven-over-simulated-substrate
    From here the space forks wide — real history, fantasy settings, game and
    story worlds — anything from the dawn of writing through science-fiction
    mechanics. The phase-transitions end; authored worlds begin.
    |charge[written-language] :tag gate
      :opened-by "8.language"
      Written language — with whatever agent/intelligence substrate it
      requires, and most of what every prior phase built. Thought moves back
      out of the timestream; history becomes possible, and the world's record
      is no longer only geological but documentary.
    |promises
      |promise[written-record].state :from written-language
        History — a documentary record, institutions, accumulated and
        correctable knowledge; the world can now inherit INTENTIONS.
    |record
      The written layer — the first record the world keeps of itself, on
      purpose.
